# React Patterns

## Component folder (required)

Every non-trivial component is a folder:

```
ComponentName/
  ComponentName.tsx    ← component logic
  ComponentName.css    ← scoped styles
  index.ts             ← export { ComponentName } from './ComponentName';
```

## Components

- Functional only; no class components.
- Explicit `interface FooProps`; no `any`.
- Pages orchestrate; child components render.
- Handle loading, error, and empty states — always.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — no states, fetch in render
export function ProjectsPage() {
  const [rows, setRows] = useState([]);
  fetch('/api/projects').then(r => r.json()).then(setRows);
  return <Table data={rows} />;
}

// ✅ GOOD
export function ProjectsPage() {
  const { projects, isLoading, error } = useProjects();
  if (isLoading) return <PageSpinner />;
  if (error) return <ErrorState message={error.message} />;
  return <ProjectsTable rows={projects} />;
}
```

## Hooks

- Prefix `use`; one concern per hook.
- Async hooks return `{ data, isLoading, error, refetch? }`.
- Clean up effects (return cleanup from `useEffect`).

## API

- All HTTP through `@api/client.ts → apiRequest<T>()`.
- No hardcoded `localhost` anywhere in `apps/web/src/`.
- Async API functions end with `Async`.
- Handle `ApiError`; surface `err.message` to users in Hebrew.

## CSS — camelCase BEM

```css
.projectDrawer { }           /* block */
.projectDrawer__header { }   /* element */
.projectDrawer--open { }     /* modifier */
```

- CSS variables only; no magic numbers.
- No global selectors inside component CSS.
- Co-locate with component: `ProjectDrawer.css` next to `ProjectDrawer.tsx`.

## State

- Local UI → `useState`
- Auth/session → `api/auth.ts` (sessionStorage, never React state)
- Avoid prop drilling 3+ levels — use context or composition

## Naming quick reference

| Item | Pattern | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Component file | PascalCase | `ProjectDrawer.tsx` |
| Hook file | camelCase | `useProjects.ts` |
| API function | verb + entity + `Async` | `getProjectLifecycleAsync` |
| Props type | Component + `Props` | `ProjectDrawerProps` |
| Handler | `handle` + action | `handleSaveProject` |
| Boolean state | `is`/`has`/`can` prefix | `isEditMode` |
